  "texts": [
    "Its versatility was showcased through the successful completion of four comprehensive case studies, demonstrating its broad applicability across diverse analytical scenarios.",
    "Recently, we implemented in-line Raman spectroscopy to monitor the real-time conversion of styrene to polystyrene, utilizing a custom Python package de-veloped in-house [53].",
    "This approach enabled us to track the conversion process at different residence times.",
    "Specifically, we quantified the conversion by analyzing the area under the curve (AUC) of the Raman-active vibrational modes associated with the styrene-vinyl C=C stretch (≈1630 cm -1), which we calibrated against signals from p-xylene (≈830 cm -1).",
    "To resolve overlapping peaks, we employed curve-fitting techniques utilizing Lorentzian functional forms, facilitated by the lmfit Python package."
